&lt;h2&gt;About Isolocity&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Isolocity is a quality management software (QMS) company built for modern manufacturers. Our AI-powered platform helps teams streamline compliance, manage non-conformances, and maintain audit readiness across regulated industries including aerospace, medical devices, cannabis, and food production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re remote-first, fast-growing, and committed to helping operations teams work smarter through automation and intelligent tooling, reflecting the same principles we champion for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the Position&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Operations Systems Manager owns and optimizes the internal systems and workflows that power Isolocity&#39;s business operations, serving as the connective tissue between teams to ensure tools, automation, and data flows stay aligned, efficient, and scalable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate thinks in systems, communicates clearly across functions, treats AI-assisted workflows as standard practice: equally comfortable building a no-code automation, partnering with leadership on strategy, and documenting the SOPs that keep the organization running.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What Success Looks Like&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In your first 30 days, you&#39;ve mapped the current tech stack, identified the top three workflow gaps, and built your first automation in production. By 90 days, cross-functional teams are relying on your dashboards, onboarding is smoother, and at least one manual process has been eliminated. At six months, you are the operational backbone of the company: the person everyone comes to when something needs to be built, integrated, or documented. Leadership trusts your data, your processes run quietly in the background, and you&#39;re already planning what comes next.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Systems Ownership&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own, administer, and continuously optimize the company&#39;s core operational tools, including CRM, project management, communication platforms, and internal QMS, ensuring integrations are clean, data is accurate, and workflows are built to scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the internal authority on how systems connect and interact, proactively resolving gaps before they become bottlenecks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Automation &amp;amp; AI Workflows&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and maintain no-code and low-code automations using platforms such as Zapier, Make, n8n, or equivalent tools to eliminate manual work and accelerate team output.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement opportunities to embed AI tools into day-to-day workflows, covering everything from drafting and summarization to data processing and routing, raising the operational baseline across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Cross-Functional Coordination&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the operational bridge between Sales, Customer Success, Product, and Leadership, translating business needs into system logic, workflow configurations, and process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate alignment across teams by ensuring that tooling decisions and workflow changes are communicated clearly and implemented without disruption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Operations, Data &amp;amp; Continuous Improvement&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain data pipelines and dashboards that give leadership real-time visibility into KPIs and team performance; enforce data governance standards across all operational systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document systems, automations, and SOPs as a single source of truth, keeping knowledge accessible and transferable as the team scales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and manage third-party tools and vendors; negotiate contracts and keep the tech stack right-sized and cost-effective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage timelines and coordinate stak

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Our customer is the maker of the world’s first carbon fiber performance insole trusted by 600+ professional and collegiate sports programs, Olympians, and hundreds of thousands of athletes striving to improve performance and recovery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;As the company continues to scale its direct-to-consumer business beyond a $45M+ run rate, they are expanding into additional recovery and footwear products including clogs and slides while investing heavily in creative performance marketing across Meta and TikTok.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The company operates with a lean, fast-moving, highly collaborative culture where creative execution, testing velocity, and performance insights directly impact business growth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;About the Position&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We are seeking a Performance Creative Strategist to help drive scalable direct-response creative across Meta and TikTok advertising channels. This role will work closely with the VP of Marketing and Director of Content to develop high-performing creative concepts rooted in biomechanics, athlete performance stories, recovery insights, and real customer outcomes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;This position owns the creative testing roadmap, angle development, creative briefing process, and post-launch performance analysis. The strategist will collaborate directly with internal editors, UGC creators, athlete talent, and external agencies to ensure creative execution aligns with performance goals and brand standards.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;This is a hybrid role based in Milford, Connecticut with in-office collaboration required Tuesday through Thursday.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Key responsibilities include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Build and maintain a living “angle library” including hooks, objections, athlete insights, reviews, and creative concepts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Develop and manage a weekly creative testing roadmap with 5–10 new concepts per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Write detailed creative briefs and storyboard concepts for editors and creators&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Provide detailed creative direction and frame-level feedback on video content and ad variations&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remote Senior Desktop Software Developer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Sync&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Sync.com is a leading end-to-end encrypted cloud storage platform operating at significant scale across dual data centers. We build secure, privacy-first software that millions of users trust with their most important files. Our desktop applications are the front line of that trust—running on Mac, Linux, and Windows, syncing data reliably and securely across every platform.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We’re rebuilding our desktop application from the ground up. Our current clients are built on native, platform-specific stacks (C++/Swift and friends), and we’re consolidating onto a unified, modern Rust-based architecture across macOS, Linux, and Windows—treated as first-class, equal targets.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We’re looking for a Senior Desktop Software Developer to be the technical owner of this greenfield rewrite. This is a high-ownership individual contributor role: you’ll architect the new application, define how we build and ship it, and set the engineering quality bar from day one. You won’t have direct reports, but you will set the standard that the desktop product is measured against.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilties&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Lead a greenfield rewrite of our desktop client, migrating from native platform-specific code to a unified Rust-based architecture.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Own the complete desktop SDLC—architecture, implementation, release engineering, and ongoing maintenance—across macOS, Linux, and Windows as equal priorities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Tackle the genuinely hard problems end to end: sync engine internals, deep OS file-system integration, and robust update/release infrastructure—all of which we consider equally critical.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Design and operate a secure auto-updater: signed delivery, signature verification, staged rollouts, rollback, and reliable cross-platform update mechanics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Define the quality bar for the new codebase from scratch—test strategy, automated coverage, CI/CD, observability, and crash reporting—and hold the product to it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-s

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;About The Ocean Cleanup&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The Ocean Cleanup is a global nonprofit that develops and scales solutions to rid the world’s oceans of plastic, driving systemic change, and creating a lasting positive impact for people, wildlife, and the planet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The HR team plays a vital role in making that mission possible by enabling our people to thrive. We translate ambition into action by attracting purpose-driven talent, supporting our teams through every stage of the employee journey, ensuring full compliance with employment laws and payroll processes, and providing learning &amp;amp; development support to all our staff members.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;About the Position&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We are looking for a Senior People Business Partner who will act as an Employee Champion and Change Agent. The position is responsible for aligning business objectives with employees and management in designated teams. For the right candidate this role could involve managing the People Business Partner and Operations Team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;As a Senior People Business Partner, you will serve as a strategic sparring partner, aligning business needs with People &amp;amp; Organization initiatives while acting as the primary HR contact. You will drive organizational health by optimizing structures to meet business goals and coach managers on performance management and employee development. Your role includes providing expertise in employee relations, feedback, compensation, and organizational development, while building strong stakeholder relationships across the business.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Set clear direction for the Business Partner function and define how the team engages with and enables the business.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Act as a sparring partner and work with the business to identify business needs and requirements, serving as the point of contact for all People &amp;amp; Organization matters.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Shape and drive People strategies across a global workforce, ensuring alignment across regions and business priorities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Build and drive organizational health by ensuring the organization is structured to achieve business objectives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; li

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Realist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Realist is an innovative WealthTech startup based in Germany, committed to transforming the financial industry through cutting-edge technology, data-driven insights, and scalable financial infrastructure. As we expand our platform and technology capabilities, we are looking for an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Senior Software Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to join our growing team in Berlin and help build the next generation of financial systems.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Software Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;, you will play a key role in designing and building high-performance financial systems that process large volumes of data reliably and securely. You will work closely with product, engineering, and data teams to architect scalable systems and contribute to the development of intelligent, AI-driven financial applications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;This role requires strong experience in &lt;strong&gt;backend engineering, distributed systems, and data-intensive architectures&lt;/strong&gt;, combined with a mindset suited for a fast-moving startup environment. We are particularly looking for someone who is a fast learner, able to quickly adapt to new technologies and evolving challenges.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Design, develop, and maintain scalable backend systems supporting data-intensive financial applications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Build and optimize &lt;strong&gt;high-performance OLTP systems&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;for transaction-heavy workloads.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Contribute to &lt;strong&gt;system architecture and design&lt;/strong&gt;, ensuring reliability, scalability, and maintainability.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Work with cloud infrastructure, particularly AWS, to deploy and manage production-grade services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Develop services using &lt;strong&gt;Node.js, python and C#&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;within modern microservice architectures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Collaborate with data and engineering teams on&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;data pipeline and OLAP system design&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;where applicable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Implement and maintain &lt;strong&gt;AI-enabled features&lt;/strong&gt;, including the development of &lt;strong&gt;agentic systems&lt;/strong&gt; and AI-powered workflows.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Apply modern AI engineering practices including &lt;strong&gt;LLM integration, evaluation frameworks (Evals), and guardrails&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&g
